Motocross fanatics flocked to the local race track in full force on Saturday showing off their skills while competing for a podium position. This was the first eventful race since the national lockdown restrictions were eased for sporting events.
It was the biggest event in Polokwane since the beginning of lockdown and riders gathered and competed in various classes and age groups.
Organiser of the event, Dean Rudiger confirmed that the event was a great success for riders and fans and they look forward to the next event.
Story: Riana Joubert